#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.22"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.22:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.22:0.2"
msgid "3. Gahapativagga "
msgstr "3. Householders "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 22. Dutiyauggasutta → hatthigāmakauggasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.22:0.3"
msgid "22. Dutiyauggasutta "
msgstr "22. With Ugga of the Village of Hatthi "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an8.22:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vajjīsu viharati hatthigāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Vajjis at the village of Hatthi. "

msgctxt "an8.22:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "an8.22:1.3"
msgid "“aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, acchariyehi abbhutehi dhammehi samannāgataṃ uggaṃ gahapatiṃ hatthigāmakaṃ dhārethā”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, you should remember the householder Ugga of Hatthi as someone who has eight amazing and incredible qualities.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.22:1.4"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "an8.22:1.5"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi. "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his dwelling. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.213, sc2
msgctxt "an8.22:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena uggassa gahapatino hatthigāmakassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then a certain mendicant robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of the householder Ugga of Hatthi, where he sat on the seat spread out. "

msgctxt "an8.22:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho uggo gahapati hatthigāmako yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho uggaṃ gahapatiṃ hatthigāmakaṃ so bhikkhu etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Ugga of Hatthi went up to that mendicant, bowed, and sat down to one side. The mendicant said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.22:2.3"
msgid "“aṭṭhahi kho tvaṃ, gahapati, acchariyehi abbhutehi dhammehi samannāgato bhagavatā byākato. "
msgstr "“Householder, the Buddha declared that you have eight amazing and incredible qualities. "

msgctxt "an8.22:2.4"
msgid "Katame te, gahapati, aṭṭha acchariyā abbhutā dhammā, yehi tvaṃ samannāgato bhagavatā byākato”ti? "
msgstr "What are the eight qualities that he spoke of?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an8.22:3.1"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, bhante, jānāmi: "
msgstr "“Sir, I don’t know "

msgctxt "an8.22:3.2"
msgid "‘katamehi aṭṭhahi acchariyehi abbhutehi dhammehi samannāgato bhagavatā byākato’ti. "
msgstr "what eight amazing and incredible qualities the Buddha was referring to. "

msgctxt "an8.22:3.3"
msgid "Api ca, bhante, ye me aṭṭha acchariyā abbhutā dhammā saṃvijjanti, "
msgstr "But these eight amazing and incredible qualities are found in me. "

msgctxt "an8.22:3.4"
msgid "taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.22:3.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, gahapatī”ti kho so bhikkhu uggassa gahapatino hatthigāmakassa paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, householder,” replied the mendicant. "

msgctxt "an8.22:3.6"
msgid "Uggo gahapati hatthigāmako etadavoca: "
msgstr "Ugga of Hatthi said this: "

# NOTE: Nagavana might be a wood where elephants are found. But I think it’s unlikely you’d be partying in such a dangerous place. It was common for the areas around shrines for local deities to be kept clear and pleasant and it is such a place that I think the text refers to.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.22:3.7"
msgid "“yadāhaṃ, bhante, nāgavane paricaranto bhagavantaṃ paṭhamaṃ dūratova addasaṃ; "
msgstr "“Sir, when I first saw the Buddha off in the distance I was partying in the Dragon’s Park. "

msgctxt "an8.22:3.8"
msgid "saha dassaneneva me, bhante, bhagavato cittaṃ pasīdi, surāmado ca pahīyi. "
msgstr "My heart was inspired as soon as I saw him, and I sobered up. "

msgctxt "an8.22:3.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhante, paṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo saṃvijjati. (1) "
msgstr "This is the first incredible and amazing quality found in me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.214, sc4
msgctxt "an8.22:4.1"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, bhante, pasannacitto bhagavantaṃ payirupāsiṃ. "
msgstr "With confident heart I paid homage to the Buddha. "

msgctxt "an8.22:4.2"
msgid "Tassa me bhagavā anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The Buddha taught me step by step, with "

msgctxt "an8.22:4.3"
msgid "dānakathaṃ sīlakathaṃ saggakathaṃ; "
msgstr "a talk on giving, ethical conduct, and heaven. "

msgctxt "an8.22:4.4"
msgid "kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ, nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi. "
msgstr "He explained the drawbacks of sensual pleasures, so sordid and corrupt, and the benefit of renunciation. "

msgctxt "an8.22:4.5"
msgid "Yadā maṃ bhagavā aññāsi kallacittaṃ muducittaṃ vinīvaraṇacittaṃ udaggacittaṃ pasannacittaṃ, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā taṃ pakāsesi—"
msgstr "And when he knew that my mind was ready, pliable, rid of hindrances, joyful, and confident he explained the special teaching of the Buddhas: "

msgctxt "an8.22:4.6"
msgid "dukkhaṃ, samudayaṃ, nirodhaṃ, maggaṃ. "
msgstr "suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path. "

msgctxt "an8.22:4.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ paṭiggaṇheyya; "
msgstr "Just as a clean cloth rid of stains would properly absorb dye, "

msgctxt "an8.22:4.8"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho me tasmiṃyeva āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi: "
msgstr "in that very seat the stainless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in me: "

msgctxt "an8.22:4.9"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman’ti. "
msgstr "‘Everything that has a beginning has an end.’ "

msgctxt "an8.22:4.10"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhadhammo pattadhammo viditadhammo pariyogāḷhadhammo tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṅkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane tattheva buddhañca dhammañca saṅghañca saraṇaṃ agamāsiṃ, brahmacariyapañcamāni ca sikkhāpadāni samādiyiṃ. "
msgstr "I saw, attained, understood, and fathomed the Dhamma. I went beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and became self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instructions. Right there I went for refuge to the Buddha, his teaching, and the Saṅgha. And I undertook the five training rules with celibacy as the fifth. "

msgctxt "an8.22:4.11"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhante, dutiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo saṃvijjati. (2) "
msgstr "This is the second incredible and amazing quality found in me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an8.22:5.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, catasso komāriyo pajāpatiyo ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "I had four teenage wives. "

msgctxt "an8.22:5.2"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, bhante, yena tā pajāpatiyo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā tā pajāpatiyo etadavacaṃ: "
msgstr "And I went to them and said: "

msgctxt "an8.22:5.3"
msgid "‘mayā kho, bhaginiyo, brahmacariyapañcamāni sikkhāpadāni samādinnāni. "
msgstr "‘Sisters, I’ve undertaken the five training rules with celibacy as fifth. "

msgctxt "an8.22:5.4"
msgid "Yā icchati sā idheva bhoge ca bhuñjatu puññāni ca karotu, sakāni vā ñātikulāni gacchatu. "
msgstr "If you wish, you may stay here, enjoy my wealth, and do good deeds. Or you can return to your own families. "

msgctxt "an8.22:5.5"
msgid "Hoti vā pana purisādhippāyo, kassa vo dammī’ti? "
msgstr "Or would you prefer if I gave you to another man?’ "

msgctxt "an8.22:5.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sā, bhante, jeṭṭhā pajāpati maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When I said this, my eldest wife said to me: "

msgctxt "an8.22:5.7"
msgid "‘itthannāmassa maṃ, ayyaputta, purisassa dehī’ti. "
msgstr "‘My lord, please give me to such-and-such a man.’ "

msgctxt "an8.22:5.8"
msgid "Atha kho ahaṃ, bhante, taṃ purisaṃ pakkosāpetvā vāmena hatthena pajāpatiṃ gahetvā dakkhiṇena hatthena bhiṅgāraṃ gahetvā tassa purisassa oṇojesiṃ. "
msgstr "Then I summoned that man. Taking my wife with my left hand and a ceremonial vase with my right, I presented her to that man with the pouring of water. "

msgctxt "an8.22:5.9"
msgid "Komāriṃ kho panāhaṃ, bhante, dāraṃ pariccajanto nābhijānāmi cittassa aññathattaṃ. "
msgstr "But I can’t recall getting upset while giving away my teenage wife. "

msgctxt "an8.22:5.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhante, tatiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo saṃvijjati. (3) "
msgstr "This is the third incredible and amazing quality found in me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an8.22:6.1"
msgid "Saṃvijjanti kho pana me, bhante, kule bhogā. "
msgstr "And though my family has wealth, "

msgctxt "an8.22:6.2"
msgid "Te ca kho appaṭivibhattā sīlavantehi kalyāṇadhammehi. "
msgstr "it’s shared without reserve with ethical people of good character. "

msgctxt "an8.22:6.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhante, catuttho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo saṃvijjati. (4) "
msgstr "This is the fourth incredible and amazing quality found in me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.215, sc7
msgctxt "an8.22:7.1"
msgid "Yaṃ kho panāhaṃ, bhante, bhikkhuṃ payirupāsāmi; "
msgstr "When I pay homage to a mendicant, "

msgctxt "an8.22:7.2"
msgid "sakkaccaṃyeva payirupāsāmi, no asakkaccaṃ. "
msgstr "I do so carefully, not carelessly. "

msgctxt "an8.22:7.3"
msgid "So ce me āyasmā dhammaṃ deseti; "
msgstr "If that venerable teaches me the Dhamma, "

msgctxt "an8.22:7.4"
msgid "sakkaccaṃyeva suṇomi, no asakkaccaṃ. "
msgstr "I listen carefully, not carelessly. "

msgctxt "an8.22:7.5"
msgid "No ce me so āyasmā dhammaṃ deseti, ahamassa dhammaṃ desemi. "
msgstr "But if they don’t teach me the Dhamma, I teach them. "

msgctxt "an8.22:7.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhante, pañcamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo saṃvijjati. (5) "
msgstr "This is the fifth incredible and amazing quality found in me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an8.22:8.1"
msgid "Anacchariyaṃ kho pana, bhante, saṃghe nimantite devatā upasaṅkamitvā ārocenti: "
msgstr "It’s not unusual for deities to come to me when the Saṅgha has been invited and announce: "

#. VAR: diṭṭhippatto → diṭṭhappatto (mr)
msgctxt "an8.22:8.2"
msgid "‘asuko, gahapati, bhikkhu ubhatobhāgavimutto asuko paññāvimutto asuko kāyasakkhī asuko diṭṭhippatto asuko saddhāvimutto asuko dhammānusārī asuko saddhānusārī asuko sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo asuko dussīlo pāpadhammo’ti. "
msgstr "‘Householder, that mendicant is freed both ways. That one is freed by wisdom. That one is a personal witness. That one is attained to view. That one is freed by faith. That one is a follower of the teachings. That one is a follower by faith. That one is ethical, of good character. That one is unethical, of bad character.’ "

msgctxt "an8.22:8.3"
msgid "Saṃghaṃ kho panāhaṃ, bhante, parivisanto nābhijānāmi evaṃ cittaṃ uppādento: "
msgstr "But while I’m serving the Saṅgha I don’t recall thinking: "

msgctxt "an8.22:8.4"
msgid "‘imassa vā thokaṃ demi imassa vā bahukan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Let me give this one just a little, and that one a lot.’ "

msgctxt "an8.22:8.5"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, bhante, samacittova demi. "
msgstr "Rather, I give impartially. "

msgctxt "an8.22:8.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhante, chaṭṭho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo saṃvijjati. (6) "
msgstr "This is the sixth incredible and amazing quality found in me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#. VAR: Anacchariyaṃ → acchariyaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.22:9.1"
msgid "Anacchariyaṃ kho pana maṃ, bhante, devatā upasaṅkamitvā ārocenti: "
msgstr "It’s not unusual for deities to come to me and announce: "

msgctxt "an8.22:9.2"
msgid "‘svākkhāto, gahapati, bhagavatā dhammo’ti. "
msgstr "‘Householder, the Buddha’s teaching is well explained!’ "

msgctxt "an8.22:9.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, tā devatā evaṃ vademi: "
msgstr "When they say this I say to them: "

msgctxt "an8.22:9.4"
msgid "‘vadeyyātha vā evaṃ kho tumhe devatā no vā vadeyyātha, atha kho svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo’ti. "
msgstr "‘The Buddha’s teaching is well explained, regardless of whether or not you deities say so!’ "

msgctxt "an8.22:9.5"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ, bhante, abhijānāmi tatonidānaṃ cittassa unnatiṃ: "
msgstr "But I don’t recall getting too excited by the fact that "

msgctxt "an8.22:9.6"
msgid "‘maṃ tā devatā upasaṅkamanti, ahaṃ vā devatāhi saddhiṃ sallapāmī’ti. "
msgstr "the deities come to me, and I have a conversation with them. "

msgctxt "an8.22:9.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhante, sattamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo saṃvijjati. (7) "
msgstr "This is the seventh incredible and amazing quality found in me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.216, sc10
msgctxt "an8.22:10.1"
msgid "Sace kho panāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato paṭhamataraṃ kālaṃ kareyyaṃ, anacchariyaṃ kho panetaṃ yaṃ maṃ bhagavā evaṃ byākareyya: "
msgstr "If I pass away before the Buddha, it wouldn’t be surprising if the Buddha declares of me: "

msgctxt "an8.22:10.2"
msgid "‘natthi taṃ saṃyojanaṃ yena saṃyutto uggo gahapati hatthigāmako puna imaṃ lokaṃ āgaccheyyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The householder Ugga of Hatthi is bound by no fetter that might return him to this world.’ "

msgctxt "an8.22:10.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhante, aṭṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo saṃvijjati. (8) "
msgstr "This is the eighth incredible and amazing quality found in me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an8.22:11.1"
msgid "Ime kho me, bhante, aṭṭha acchariyā abbhutā dhammā saṃvijjanti. "
msgstr "These eight amazing and incredible qualities are found in me. "

msgctxt "an8.22:11.2"
msgid "Na ca kho ahaṃ jānāmi: "
msgstr "But I don’t know "

msgctxt "an8.22:11.3"
msgid "‘katamehi cāhaṃ aṭṭhahi acchariyehi abbhutehi dhammehi samannāgato bhagavatā byākato’”ti. "
msgstr "what eight amazing and incredible qualities the Buddha was referring to.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an8.22:12.1"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu uggassa gahapatino hatthigāmakassa nivesane piṇḍapātaṃ gahetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then that mendicant, after taking alms-food in Ugga of Hatthi’s home, got up from his seat and left. "

msgctxt "an8.22:12.2"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then after the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. "

msgctxt "an8.22:12.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu yāvatako ahosi uggena gahapatinā hatthigāmakena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo, taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi. "
msgstr "He informed the Buddha of all he had discussed with the householder Ugga of the village of Hatthi. The Buddha said: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an8.22:13.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhu. "
msgstr "“Good, good, mendicant! "

msgctxt "an8.22:13.2"
msgid "Yathā taṃ uggo gahapati hatthigāmako sammā byākaramāno byākareyya, imeheva kho, bhikkhu, aṭṭhahi acchariyehi abbhutehi dhammehi samannāgato uggo gahapati hatthigāmako mayā byākato. "
msgstr "When I declared that the householder Ugga of the village of Hatthi was someone who has eight amazing and incredible qualities, I was referring to the same eight qualities that he rightly explained to you. "

msgctxt "an8.22:13.3"
msgid "Imehi ca pana, bhikkhu, aṭṭhahi acchariyehi abbhutehi dhammehi samannāgataṃ uggaṃ gahapatiṃ hatthigāmakaṃ dhārehī”ti. "
msgstr "You should remember the householder Ugga of Hatthi as someone who has these eight amazing and incredible qualities.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.22:13.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

